        "answer": "LPR (Loan Prime Rate) is the loan market quoted rate, formed by 18 quoting banks adding points to the MLF rate. Currently, the 1-year LPR is 3.45%, and the 5-year+ LPR is 4.20%. New bank loans mainly reference LPR for pricing, while existing loans adjust at annual repricing dates."
